@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy for Student Management System";
    ViewData["Update"] = "10-08-2025";
}

<link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/stylePrivacy.css" />
<div class="content">
    <div class="container">
    <h2>@ViewData["Title"]</h2>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: @ViewData["Update"]</p>

        <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard student information when you use our Student Management System. 
            This System is built on ASP.NET MVC framework with PostgreSQL database backend.</p>

        <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p>We collect the following student information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Student ID (unique identifier)</li>
            <li>Full name</li>
            <li>Phone number</li>
            <li>Physical address</li>
            <li>Email address</li>            
        </ul>

        <h3>3. How We Use the Information</h3>
        <p>The collected information is used for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Creating and managing student records</li>
            <li>Academic administration purposes</li>
            <li>System authentication and authorization</li>
            <li>Communication with students</li>
            <li>Improving system functionality</li>          
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Data Storage and Security</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>All data is stored in a PostgreSQL database</li>
            <li>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal data</li>
            <li>Access to student information is restricted to authorized personnel only</li>          
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Data Retention</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Student records are retained as long as necessary for educational purposes</li>            
            <li>Proper deletion procedures are followed when data is no longer needed</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
        <p>Student information may be shared with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Authorized school administrators and faculty</li>
            <li>Third-party service providers (under confidentiality agreements)</li>
            <li>When required by law or legal process</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell or rent student information to third parties.</p>

        <h3>7. User Rights</h3>
        <p>Students have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access their personal information</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of their data</li>         
        </ul>

        <h3>8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
        <p>Our System may use:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Session cookies for authentication</li>
            <li>Necessary functional cookies</li>
            <li>Analytics cookies to improve user experience</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>9. Changes to This Policy</h3>
        <p>We may update this policy periodically. Users will be notified of significant changes.</p>

        <h3>10. Contact Information</h3>
        <div class="contact-info">
            <p>For privacy-related inquiries, please contact:</p>
            <p>
            GitHub : <a href="https://github.com/thetnaing-dh">Thet Naing Oo</a><br>
            Email : <a href="mailto:thetnaing94@gmail.com">thetnaing94@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
        </div>           
    </div>
</div>
